&lt;p&gt;DoorDash is building the world’s most reliable on-demand logistics platform. As part of our global expansion, we are investing heavily in Brazil and growing our engineering presence in São Paulo. This is a unique opportunity to join one of Silicon Valley’s fastest-growing companies—while staying close to home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Backend Engineers who are excited to solve real-world problems at scale. You’ll work on product teams or platform teams that power our three-sided marketplace of &lt;strong&gt;Consumers, Dashers, and Merchants&lt;/strong&gt;. From improving restaurant discovery to optimizing delivery logistics, you’ll help shape the experience of millions of users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work alongside experienced engineers, product managers, and designers—many based in the U.S.—so fluency in English and strong collaboration skills are essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain large-scale backend systems used by millions of users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to our technical roadmap and define the architecture for key product areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive improvements in performance, scalability, reliability, and security&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help transition parts of our monolithic codebase to a microservices architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams across Brazil and the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on high-impact features that directly improve the user experience for Dashers, Merchants, or Consumers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
